\u201d, a piano solo.\nThe second part will tell of\nthe birth of the Christ child.\nBible verses will be read by Dav\nid Olle, Kenneth Heiskanen and\nGerald Lillstrang of Miss Anita\nMalkamawi's class.\nLou\nKiikka\nwill\nMiss Marie\ndirect\nthe\nYounger Girls\u2019 choir in \u201cSilent\nNight\u201d and \"O Little Town of\nBethlehem\u201d.\nPart three, The Holy Night,\nwill start with an\nexercise by\nDennis Gray, Audrey, Kautian\nen, Charles Hill and Carol Pern\noja,\nnursery\nchildren. Kayette\nHakola will give the Bible read\ning. The Older Girls\u2019 choir will\nsing \u201cWhile Shepherds Watched\nTheir Flocks\u201d and \u201cThere Were\nShepherds under the direction\nof Mrs. Lillian Oinonen.\nMiner\nIlUHILUUIS\npi U\ngram are: Bible reading by Joan\nKriikku;\nHighest\u201d\n\u201cGlory to God in the\nby the girls\u2019 choirs;\nBible verse by Margaret Pasan\nen;\nand\nchildren\nCampana,\nexercise\nLinda\nby primary\nShirley\nKuivila.\nBrown\nDavid,\nand\nArthur Lagerstedt.\n\u201cAway in A Manger\u201d and \u201cA\nLovely Story\u201d\nchildren;\nexercise\nby the nursery\nchildren Karen\nBraski.\nby nursery\nSharon\nOJanpa and Carlene Kellhofer;\nand\nsong\nby the intermediate\ndepartment, \u201cThere Is No Name\nSo Sweet On Earth\u201d.\n\u201cO Come\nAll\nYe\nFaithful\u201d\nand \u201cWe Three Kings of Orient\nAre\u201d by the Boys\u2019 choir with\nreadings by Delbert Keltto and\nDavid Hilston;\nBible\nreadings\nby Robert Potti, Ernest Karhu i\nand\nDonald\nKangas;\nby four primary children:\nna\nHokkanen,\nJanice Lepisto and\nTommy\nexercise\nDon\nLasko,\nPatty Hil\nston; and songs by primary chil\ndren: \u201cWhat Can I Give Him?\u201d\nand \u201cI Heard The Bells\u201d.\nRecitation\nby Allan Nuuja,\nNiles Kinmen, David Ivary and\nJames\nWakkila;\n'\u2018Christmas\nMelodies\u201d, piano duet, by Fran\nces Hilston and Helmi Ann Hut\nander;\nprayer\npoem\nby Helen\nBradley and recitation by Char\nmaine Wolvin.\nOffertory\nName\nHymnal\nof\n\u201cHow Sweet 